{\pard\sb200\sa80\b\f1\fs28 What You Have Learned\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Here is a summary of the skills covered across all seven chapters:\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 1 - Account Setup: Downloading Discord, Creating your account, verifying your email, and setting up your profile.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 2 - Interface Navigation: Discord's panels, locating the user controls bar, search, and the Home screen.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 3 - Joining Servers: Using an invite link, navigating the discovery page, and understanding a new server.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 4 - Text Channels: Sending, replying, reacting, editing, deleting, uploading, and using @mentions.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 5 - Direct Messages: Creating DMs and group DMs, using the DM inbox, and professional etiquette.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 6 - Voice Channels: Operating efficiently in voice channels, from joining one, to muting, deafening, volume control, screen sharing, and leaving.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ch. 7 - Settings: Maximizing your experience through settings, including notifications, status modes, appearance, privacy, and safety.\par}
