{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Running into an issue and don't know what to do? Here are the answers to some common problems new users run into.\par}
{\pard\sb200\sa80\b\f1\fs28 Messaging and Channels\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Why can't I type in certain channels?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 This is quite common, and typically intentional. It usually relates to one of the following:\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Read-Only channels: These channels are not intended for conversation. They only allow messages from administrators, such as announcements.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Your assigned role does not have permission to message in that channel. DM a server administrator to request a role with permission.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  Upon joining the first time, some servers require you to acknowledge the rules before messaging. Check for a rule channel and read the provided instructions for acknowledging the rules.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 How do I find a server I've already joined?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 The server list sidebar on the far left contains every server you are in, represented by circular icons. Hover over those icons to reveal each server's name. Then click the icon to open it.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 How do I leave a server I no longer need?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Focus on the server sidebar. Find the intended server's circular icon, and right-click it. A context menu appears. Click "Leave Server." Click Leave Server again on the confirmation screen. The server is now gone from your server sidebar.\par}
{\pard\sb200\sa80\b\f1\fs28 Audio and Voice\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Why am I not hearing anyone in a voice channel?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Work through these checks in order:\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Locate the headphone icon in the user control bar on the bottom left. If the headphone has a red slash, you are deafened. Click it to undeafen.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Check your system volume. Ensure the volume on your PC or Laptop is set to an audible level.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Click the Discord Settings icon resembling a gear, click Voice & Video, and check your Output Device.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 If you have multiple output devices, test each one until audio transmits via the expected device such as headphones or speakers.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Scroll down Voice & Video to find "Sounds." Click Preview Sound on each sound effect to test for audio output.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Why is my microphone not working?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Try the following steps:\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Locate the microphone icon in the user control bar on the bottom left. If the microphone has a red slash, you are muted. Click it to unmute.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Click the Settings icon, click Voice & Video, and check your Input Device.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 If you have multiple input devices, test each one by clicking the "Mic Test" Button. A working microphone will produce a visual output showing your microphone's volume.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Enable microphone permissions for Discord:\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  On Windows, click your Windows key, open Settings, hit Privacy, and then pick Microphone. Locate the Discord app, ensuring it is enabled.\par}
{\pard\li400\fi-200\sa60\f0\fs22 \bullet  On macOS, open the Settings app in the toolbar, choose Privacy & Security, and select Microphone. Locate the Discord app, ensuring it is enabled.\par}
{\pard\sb200\sa80\b\f1\fs28 Account and Privacy\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Can other people see my email address or real name?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 No. Users can only see your chosen display name and username. Whether you want to use your real name as a display name is your choice and may be appropriate in academic or work settings.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Someone is acting inappropriately. What do I do?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Take the following steps:\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Block the user: Right-click their name, click Block. They will not be able to DM you or see your messages in servers.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Report the message: If their message breaks Discord Terms of Service, Right-click any message and select Report Message. A report menu opens. Follow the prompts to submit your report.\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Notify your server administrator: If their message only breaks server rules, inform an administrator such as a professor or manager. They can remove or ban the user from the server.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 I'm getting too many notifications. How do I reduce them?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Find the server in your server selection panel. Right-click it. Hover over notifications and adjust your setting to Only @Mentions. You'll only be notified when you are mentioned in a message. For detailed steps, see Chapter 7: Managing Notifications.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Does Discord have a web app?\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Yes. Discord's web version has most of the features from the Desktop version, and most of the instructions in this tutorial will apply. However, the downloaded version is more suited for everyday use. Most individuals use the web version if they need to check their messages while using an unusual device, such as a hotel computer. Find the web version here: Discord.com/app.\par}
{\pard\pagebb\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Are you lost in the jargon? Use this glossary to find definitions for any Discord terminology used in this tutorial.\par}
{\pard\sb60\sa40\li360\ri360\b\f1\fs22 How to Use This Glossary\b0\par}
{\pard\sa80\li360\ri360\f0\fs22\cf3 Terms are listed alphabetically. If one of these terms is used and you are unfamiliar with it, click it to directly locate its definition here. To return to where you were, click your browser's back button.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Bot\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 Useful automated accounts that can perform many tasks from sending reminders, welcoming new members, to moderating text channels for spam and foul language via automated language filtering. Bots can only be added by administrators.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Channel\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 A specific room within a Discord server used for communication. Text channels (marked with #) are for written messages and file sharing. Voice channels (marked with a speaker icon) are for live audio conversations. Channels are organized into categories within a server.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Deafen\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 This mutes audio transmission from all other users. It also automatically mutes your own microphone. This is useful for briefly stepping away from a conversation without leaving a voice channel.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Direct Message (DM)\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 A private conversation between two Discord users, or a small group of up to 10 users, that takes place outside of any server.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Invite Link\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 The main method for granting users access to a Discord server. Invite links are a URL formatted as discord.gg/unique_code and pertain to a specific server. These are shareable across the web, email, or anywhere else, and when clicked, allow a user to join that server. They can be set to expire after a certain period or usage count.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 @Mention\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 A tag/notification method to alert a specific user. When a user's username or display name is placed directly after an @ such as in @JohnDoe, that user will receive a notification for that message (unless they have adjusted their notification settings to prevent them).\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Mute\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 A method for disabling your own microphone audio, indicated by a red slash over your microphone icon in your user control bar. You can still hear others.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Ping\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 An informal term sometimes used interchangeably with a "mention," "alert," or "notification." Pinging someone means you have sent them a DM, used @Mention to tag them in a message, or used any other method to get their attention.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Role\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 A label representing a permission group in a server. Roles are assigned by administrators or moderators and allow or prohibit members from performing a wide array of actions. In an academic setting, a "Professor" role might allow for sending announcements, editing announcements, or deleting the announcements channel altogether, while a "student" role might only allow users to read them.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Server\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 An organized community hub for a dedicated group of users. It is the main method of gathering in Discord. Your class, company department, club, or any kind of team can utilize its own Discord server. Users can join multiple different servers.\par}
{\pard\sb160\sa60\b\f1\fs24 Voice Channel\par}
{\pard\sa100\f0\fs22 The alternative to text channels. A room inside a server which enables real-time audio communication between users. These rooms are available 24/7, can be accessed by any user with the appropriate role, and require zero scheduling or prior setup for each meeting. The ideal choice for drop-in office hours. Voice channels are identifiable on the channels panel by the speaker icon before their name. Voice channels also have features like a Zoom call, such as sharing your screen.\par}
{\pard\pagebb\par}
